<h3 id="github-actions" class="headerLink">
    <a href="#github-actions" class="header-mark"></a>Github Actions</h3><p><a href="https://github.com/features/actions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Github Actions</a> is a continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) platform that allows you to automate your build, test, and deployment pipeline.
Basically speaking this allows me to automatically run <code>hugo</code> to build the static files and then upload them to my Caddy web server all from simple commit to the Github repo where I&rsquo;m storing source code.
No more manually building the static files locally on my laptop and then using SFTP to upload them to the server, it is all done for me.</p>
